In [4]:
covid_data_df['dateRep'] = pd.to_datetime(covid_data_df['dateRep'],
                                          format='%d/%m/%Y').dt.date

covid_dates = list(sorted(covid_data_df['dateRep'].unique()))
one_day = datetime.timedelta(days=1)


def autolabel(rects):
    """Attach a text label above each bar in *rects*, displaying its 
       height."""
    for rect in rects:
        height = rect.get_height()
        ax.annotate('{}'.format(height),
                    xy=(rect.get_x() + rect.get_width() / 2, height),
                    xytext=(0, 0),
                    textcoords="offset points",
                    ha='center', va='bottom')


print(f'Most recent date in file: {covid_data_df["dateRep"].max()}')

Plot top 10 countries with highest number of cases by percent of population infected

In [9]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 8))
x = np.arange(len(top_10_by_deaths['df_usa']['cases'].iloc[-30:]))

count = 0
for country in top_10_by_deaths:
    if count < 6:
        (ax.plot(x, (top_10_by_deaths[country]['cases'].iloc[-30:] /
                     top_10_by_deaths[country]['popData2018'].iloc[-30:]) *
                 100, label=top_10_by_deaths[country]
                 ['countriesAndTerritories'].iloc[0], linewidth=3))
    else:
        (ax.plot(x, (top_10_by_deaths[country]['cases'].iloc[-30:] /
                     top_10_by_deaths[country]['popData2018'].iloc[-30:]) *
                 100, label=top_10_by_deaths[country]
                 ['countriesAndTerritories'].iloc[0], linewidth=3,
                 linestyle='dashed'))
    count += 1

ax.set(ylabel="Percent of Population Infected",
       title="COVID-19 Cases\n(Percent of Population)")
ax.set_xticklabels(np.arange(min(covid_dates[-30:]), max(covid_dates[-30:]) +
                             one_day, step=1), rotation=90)
ax.set_xticks(np.arange(min(x), max(x) + 1, step=1))

ax.margins(x=0)
ax.grid(linestyle='--', linewidth=0.5)
plt.legend(loc=2)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

cases_dict = (dict(covid_data_df.groupby(['countriesAndTerritories'])
                   ['cases'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).iloc[0:10]))
labels = [country for country in cases_dict.keys()]
cases = [case for case in cases_dict.values()]

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 8))
x = np.arange(len(labels))

rects = ax.bar(x, cases, width=0.5)

autolabel(rects)
ax.set_title(label='COVID-19 Total Cases Top 10 Countries')
ax.set(xlabel="Country", ylabel="Total Cases")
ax.set_xticklabels(labels)
ax.set_xticks(x)
ax.grid(linestyle='--', linewidth=0.5)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

In [21]:
def align_yaxis(ax1, v1, ax2, v2):
    """adjust ax2 ylimit so that v2 in ax2 is aligned to v1 in ax1"""
    _, y1 = ax1.transData.transform((0, v1))
    _, y2 = ax2.transData.transform((0, v2))
    inv = ax2.transData.inverted()
    _, dy = inv.transform((0, 0)) - inv.transform((0, y1-y2))
    miny, maxy = ax2.get_ylim()
    ax2.set_ylim(miny+dy, maxy+dy)


def autolabel(rects):
    """Attach a text label above each bar in *rects*, displaying its 
       height."""
    for rect in rects:
        height = rect.get_height()
        ax.annotate(f"{height}",
                    xy=(rect.get_x() + rect.get_width() / 2, height),
                    xytext=(0, 0),
                    textcoords="offset points",
                    ha='center', va='bottom')

Maricopa County, Arizona

In [22]:
maricopa_df = (us_counties_df[us_counties_df['county'] ==
                              'Maricopa'].iloc[-30:].sort_values(by=['date']))
maricopa_tot = (us_counties_df[us_counties_df['county'] ==
                               'Maricopa'].iloc[-30:].groupby(['county'])
                               ['cases'].max()[0])
maricopa_deaths = (us_counties_df[us_counties_df['county'] ==
                                  'Maricopa'].iloc[-30:].groupby(['county'])
                   ['deaths'].max()[0])
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 8))
x = np.arange(len(maricopa_df['date']))

ax.bar(x, maricopa_df['cases'], label='Cases', width=0.6)
ax.set(ylabel="Total Cases",
       title=f"Maricopa County COVID-19\nTotal Cases: {maricopa_tot}\n"
       f"Total Deaths: {maricopa_deaths}")
ax.set_xticklabels(np.arange(min(maricopa_df['date']),
                             max(maricopa_df['date']) +
                             datetime.timedelta(days=1), step=1), rotation=90)
ax.set_xticks(np.arange(min(x), max(x)+1, step=1))

ax2 = ax.twinx()
ax2.plot(x, maricopa_df['deaths'], label='Deaths', color='r', linewidth=3)
ax2.set(ylabel='Total Deaths')
ax2.grid(b=False)

ax.set_yticks(np.linspace(int(ax.get_yticks()[0]),
                          int(ax.get_yticks()[-1]), len(ax2.get_yticks())))

h1, l1 = ax.get_legend_handles_labels()
h2, l2 = ax2.get_legend_handles_labels()
ax.legend(h1+h2, l1+l2, loc=2)

align_yaxis(ax, 0, ax2, 0)
ax.margins(x=0)
ax.grid(linestyle='--', linewidth=0.5)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

ax2.plot(x, dallas_df['deaths'], label='Deaths', color='r', linewidth=3)
ax2.set(ylabel='Total Deaths')
ax2.set_yticks(range(0, max(dallas_df['deaths'])+1, 10))
ax.set_yticks(np.linspace(int(ax.get_yticks()[0]),
                          int(ax.get_yticks()[-1]), len(ax2.get_yticks())))
ax2.grid(b=False)

h1, l1 = ax.get_legend_handles_labels()
h2, l2 = ax2.get_legend_handles_labels()
ax.legend(h1+h2, l1+l2, loc=2)

align_yaxis(ax, 0, ax2, 0)

ax.margins(x=0)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Combine DataFrame containing COVID-19 data with DataFrame containing longitude and latitude data

In [30]:
us_county_data_geo_df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['county', 'state', 'fips',
                                              'cases', 'deaths', 'long',
                                              'lat'])
us_county_data_geo_df = us_county_data_geo_df.astype({'cases': 'int64',
                                                      'deaths': 'int64'})
for idx, row in (us_counties_df.groupby(['county', 'state', 'fips'])
        [['cases', 'deaths']].sum().reset_index(level=[0, 1, 2]).iterrows()):
    if row['state'] != 'HI' and row['state'] != 'AK':
        us_county_data_geo_df.loc[idx] = [row['county'], row['state'],
                                          row['fips'], row['cases'],
                                          row['deaths'],
                                          counties_gdf[counties_gdf['FIPS'] ==
                            str(f"{int(row['fips']):05d}")]['LON'].max(),
                                          counties_gdf[counties_gdf['FIPS'] ==
                            str(f"{int(row['fips']):05d}")]['LAT'].max(), ]

points = us_county_data_geo_df.apply(lambda row: Point(row['long'],
                                                       row['lat']), axis=1)
geo_county_points = gpd.GeoDataFrame(us_county_data_geo_df, geometry=points)
geo_county_points.crs = 'epsg:4326'  # 4269, 9075, 4326
geo_county_points = geo_county_points.sort_values(by=['cases'],
                                                  ascending=False)
topn = 100

states_gdf = gpd.read_file('states/states.shp')
states_gdf.crs = 'epsg:4326'

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 8))

ax.set_aspect('equal')
ax.set_title(f"COVID-19 Top {topn} Confirmed Cases by US County\n"
             f"(Excluding HI and AK)", fontsize=20, color='w')
ax.set_axis_off()

(states_gdf[(states_gdf['STATE_NAME'] != 'Alaska') &
            (states_gdf['STATE_NAME'] != 'Hawaii')].plot(ax=ax,
                                                         color='whitesmoke',
                                                         edgecolor='black'))
for idx, row in (states_gdf[(states_gdf['STATE_NAME'] != 'Alaska') &
                        (states_gdf['STATE_NAME'] != 'Hawaii')].iterrows()):
    ax.annotate(s=row['STATE_ABBR'],
                xy=(row['geometry'].centroid.coords.xy[0][0],
                    row['geometry'].centroid.coords.xy[1][0]), ha='center',
                color='black')
geo_county_points.iloc[0:topn].plot(ax=ax, color='r', alpha=0.6,
                                markersize=geo_county_points['cases'] / 125)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Plot differnce between cases report -1 day

In [33]:
n_days = 30
y = (np.array(covid_data_df[covid_data_df['countriesAndTerritories'] ==
                        'USA']['cases'][:n_days+1].diff(periods=-1)[0:-1]))
x = (np.array(covid_data_df[covid_data_df['countriesAndTerritories'] ==
                            'USA']['dateRep'][:n_days]))
z = np.polyfit(np.arange(len(x)), y, 1)
p = np.poly1d(z)(np.arange(len(x)))

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(18, 8))

ax.set_title("COVID-19 US Cases Diff -1 Day (Last 30 Days)", fontsize=16)
ax.set(ylabel="Diff")
plt.xticks(rotation=90, ha='right', fontsize=14)

ax.bar(x, y, width=0.5, label='New Cases')
ax.plot(x, p, color='r', label='Trend', linewidth=3)

ax.legend(loc=2)
ax.grid(linestyle='--', linewidth=0.5)
ax.margins(x=0)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
